10. CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT - QUANTUM LIFELONG LEARNING

Quantum Few-Shot Learning:

```
Algorithm: Quantum Matching Networks
Support set: S = {(|x_i⟩, |y_i⟩)} few examples
Query: |x̂⟩ new patient data
Process:
1. Encode: f(|x⟩) = U(θ)|x⟩|0⟩
2. Attention: a = softmax(⟨f(x_i)|f(x̂)⟩)
3. Prediction: |ŷ⟩ = Σ a_i |y_i⟩

Advantage: Exponential speedup in similarity computation
Applications: Rare disease diagnosis from few examples
```

Catastrophic Forgetting Prevention:

```
Quantum Elastic Weight Consolidation (Q-EWC):
Fisher Information Matrix: F_ij = ⟨∂²L/∂θ_i∂θ_j⟩
Constraint: L_new(θ) = L(θ) + λ Σ F_i (θ_i - θ_i_old)²

Quantum Implementation:
F_ij measured via quantum gradient estimation
Penalty enforced via constraint Hamiltonian
Result: Retains old knowledge while learning new tasks
```

